      <div xml:id="KT360-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉāka veṟi añciya tōḻikkuc colluvāḷāyac colliyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER as one who speaks to the confidante, who
          fears the Veṟi dance, while HE was behind the hedge. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT360">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> veṟiyeṉa vuṇarnta vēla ṉōymarun</l>
          <l> taṟiyā ṉākuta laṉṉai kāṇiya</l>
          <l> varumpaṭa revva miṉṟunā muḻappiṉum</l>
          <l> vāraṟka tilla tōḻi cāraṟ</l>
          <l> piṭikkai yaṉṉa peruṅkura lēṉa</l>
          <l> luṇkiḷi kaṭiyuṅ koṭiccikaik kuḷirē</l>
          <l> cilampiṟ cilampuñ cōlai</l>
          <l> yilaṅkumalai nāṭa ṉiravi ṉāṉē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent">Even if we endure today the trouble of heavy affliction,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">for mother to see that the spear-carrying [priest],</l>
          <l rend="indent2">who contemplates [suggesting] the Veṟi dance,</l>
          <l rend="indent6">doesn't know a remedy for the pain,</l>
          <l>– may he not come, friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent">in the night, the man from a land of shining mountains</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with groves, where it is ringing like anklets:</l>
          <l rend="indent">the drum in the creeper woman's hand chasing away parakeets</l>
          <l rend="indent2">eating from the millet with ears big as the hand of a female</l>
          <l rend="indent9">elephant, on the slope.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="6+7b">
            <l>with groves, where the mere drum in the hand of the creeper woman ...</l>
            <l>rings in the mountain slopes.</l>
          </lg>
